716312f-a.title: ??Manhattan: Amsterdam Avenue - La Salle Street
716312f-a.text:
Amsterdam Avenue, west side, north from La Salle to West 125th Street. The latter point is on the right and ob-scured by the building at the N. E. corner of La Salle Street.

September, 1927
George L. Balgue, photo
716312f-a.folder: ??Amsterdam Avenue & La Salle Street, Manhattan, NY

720814f-a.text:
La Salle Place (W. 125th Street), north side, east from Amsterdam Avenue to Roosevelt Square. The converging thoroughfare at the right is the present W. 125th (formerly Manhattan) Street. Adjoining the Daniel Reeves structure is the 2 story McGuire Building and same forms the apex of this triangular block.
April 1928.
George L. Balgue,

716313f-a.text:
